article.description: Matt McCarthy had 10 points and 11 rebounds and San Francisco beat cold-shooting Radford 52-41 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: San Francisco beats cold-shooting Radford 52-41
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Matt McCarthy had 10 points and 11 rebounds and San Francisco beat cold-shooting Radford 52-41 on Tuesday night. Souley Boum added 10 points and Chase Foster had nine points on 3-of-6 shooting from long range for San Francisco (7-4), which bounced back from a 71-59 loss at Stanford on Sunday that snapped a three-game win streak. Carlik Jones scored 11 of his 19 points in the first half to lead Radford (5-6), which shot just 15 of 60 from the field (25 percent) and missed 16 of 18 3-point attempts. The Highlanders led 22-18 at halftime, but the Dons opened the second half on a 24-12 run and had a double-digit lead the rest of the way. Boum had eight points, Foster added six and Jordan Ratinho scored all five of his points during the stretch.
